In your Node.js setup, you can insert a temporary debug line in your main file after calling require('dotenv').config(). For example:

console.log(process.env.LLM_API_key);

This will print your API key to the console, confirming that it loaded correctly. Make sure to remove or comment out this line afterwards to avoid accidentally exposing your key. Also, it might be a good idea to regenerate the key if you suspect it has been exposed.
